title: Silver Green Hotel
address: No.9 ANawYaHtar Road, Yangon
descriptions: Simply decorated rooms in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant with city views.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"John12312","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is an average hotel with standard lobby. The road leading to the hotel during the day is constantly jam with heavy traffic. There are some good dining outlets nearby the hotel which is good. The hotel is also not so well known to taxi drivers. 2.Laundry service will get your clothes missing, when you ask the manager, she will tell you maybe it's somewhere in your room.
3.Most of the time the doorman will do more help than hotel manager/ receptionist. Don't argue with them, it will makes you stupid.
4.If you're looking for long term staying and have other places to choose, be sure to kindly remind the housekeeping change the pillow case and bed sheet.
5.You will never know who will call internal line to trick or treat at midnight 2 am, when I check with the counter, they just say I can do nothing for you. Suggest you unplug the internal line while sleeping.
6.If your room is facing the sun, the curtain may not help you to block all the sunshine, eye patch is needed.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel Shwe Eain Taw

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Theo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1q9-gRFTa-cXzjc58mcRbRj__l9RydXLgOSW0ZmxRcQ0xXuRm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my new favorite hotel. The prices here at the time I got here was a bargain!

You get to have free breakfast and a very large room for under $15.

Not too bad...

The only downside is the location. It is terribly far from anywhere I deem fun and exciting. It is 50 minutes away walking distance to the park. 45 minutes away from a decent gym. The market is also 20 minutes of walking.

If you are a solo traveller who loves to walk and loves affordable stays that punches above it's weight. Stay here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0YIweIXQ2WTpaUERafUUsjhqZ0YKEz5uIycz0&fid=0x0:0x1b5bc3fb87e20b49"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Steve R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked the hotel for 3 of us in a family room for 3 nights. We were running the Yangon marathon (superb) and it is 2k from the start we walked home its that close.  ||||The hotel dosnt look great with ageing decor and a tired looking exterior. Thats where the negatives stop. ||||Firstly lets put this in perspctive,our room cost 63 usd (20 bucks each) including a very nice breakfast. ||||On arrival we were greeted with an orange juice and taken to our room by 3 porters lugging our bags up 4 stories to our room. We had a fantastic view (see picture), flat screen tv with sports and movies in english, newly installed air con, en suite with electric shower (reliably warm) and comfortable beds with clean sheets and towels. What else do you want. ||||The staff are so helpful bringing up water, beers, food and anything else we needed no matter what time of the day. The breakfast is great and they even remember if you like ketchip or chilli sauce and your choice of fruit the next day. The eggs are perfect!||||On the last night I sat and watched football with the local guys on a 40" TV and we had a great laugh whilst I ate my excellent 3 dollar special fried rice packed with chicken, pork, prawns...that I had no chance of finishing due to the volume.||||All in all a fantastic place which is 15 mins from airport and anything else in the city.  With taxis costing about 3 dollars to just about anywhere.  ||||This is not the ritz but is clean, authentic with great people. I would stay here again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Canndy H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location is away from the city but transportation is not the problem as Yangon city is a TAXI city. But make sure to book in advance for daycation. Always full on weekends.

Rooms are really neat and tidy. Great for quick romantic getaways. ;)

Oh it has limited parking space on the second floor.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Su San","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3eVTgVQzYli1nWhZKF4JU47nj7GrW4Rz0-YKvBgYx6jn5vbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Quiet place to nap.
Late check out is not allowed even for 3pm though my check in was 9pm.
And our family stayed there 4 nights.
No favour was shown upon my request.
Breakfast was not up to standard like 2019.
I will look into another hotel next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Htike Aung Kyaw (ထိုက်အောင်ကျော်)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPg11AiMc4bQilh5xSPvnX1bN9Xrh58DFsOWdiTAB6ECrWVZuLrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Seems overrated. We checked-in around 3PM. Says you can check-in starting at 2PM. But when we arrived, the room wasn't quite ready yet. They were still fixing the water heater. They informed us that we'll be able to use hot water by night-time. The Side Table and Stools weren't even arranged properly when we arrived. We specifically requested the lake view room but was allocated at the 5th floor where the lake can't be seen as it's covered by trees. Still we get the view of Shwedagon Pagoda though. The room was hot, humid and a bit dusty when we checked in. Bed sheets are stained in some places but we didn't complain. What I was disgusted most by is the mold in Shower Curtains. Yuck! And hair remains in the bathtub and floor near the bed. At night, I turned on hot water and all I got was air, rusted brown water and cold water. I called them to check and they came in claiming the water is usable and is warm. It wasn't. Don't let me start with the room key card... Works 1 out of 30 tries. They came to change batteries both in the evening and the next morning. Every time we get out of the room we get locked out even though we have the key card with us. The only good thing was the tasty breakfast with a wide variety to choose from. Even for breakfast, the dining room arrangement sucked. They put two extra tables and chairs close to the buffet table and we have to tuck through these to get the food. Ugh... And they rang the doorbell at 7 AM mistakenly with the next room who were to check-out that morning. Didn't even say they were sorry for the interruption. We were given breakfast tickets but when we arrived at the dining room, no one was there to collect it so we left these tickets on the table after we were done eating. Guess what? They called us at 9AM and said it was the last call for breakfast. Good that they remind us for Breakfast, bad that they suck at who has finished eating and who have not. Overall, it seems overrated and overpriced compared to other hotels in town. Maybe they treat us locals differently from foreigners, not sure about that, as the room rates for locals and foreigners are different. But I think, for the same price, there are many hotels out there that give better service and facilities than those provided here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTjv-D6zKesrZz3a9TCruPYLhsrV5_JvBM9upK&fid=0x0:0xf4763ad7a8ba89c5"],"When":"2023-6-3"}]

descriptions: High-end hotel featuring multiple bars & restaurants, plus an outdoor pool & a spa.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bharat Vaishnav","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5qR5drKeayG4w6EzYKAKiKMIovLDH2173IofBlmVr6LTMsw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptional Stay at Chatrium Hotel Royal Lake Yangon – A Home Away from Home!

I had the pleasure of staying at Chatrium Hotel Royal Lake Yangon twice—once in May 2024 and again in February 2025—and both experiences were nothing short of exceptional. From the moment I arrived, the warm hospitality and impeccable service made me feel truly valued as a guest.

A special appreciation goes to IRIS and CRYSTAL, who went above and beyond to make my stay comfortable. Their kindness, attentiveness, and unwavering commitment to guest satisfaction were truly remarkable. No matter how busy they were, they always had a genuine smile on their faces, ensuring that every request was met with warmth and efficiency. Their positive attitude and willingness to assist made a significant difference in my overall experience.

The hotel itself is a perfect blend of luxury and tranquility, offering breathtaking views of the Royal Lake, beautifully designed rooms, and world-class amenities. The attention to detail in every aspect of the stay, from the exquisite breakfast spread to the seamless check-in and check-out process, reflects the hotel's commitment to excellence.

My heartfelt thanks to the entire Chatrium team, especially IRIS and CRYSTAL, for making my visits truly memorable. I highly recommend this hotel to anyone visiting Yangon—whether for business or leisure. Location is just perfect for a short sprint downtown for meetings or outbound to industrial zones.  You can find all dining and entertainment facilities for an evening of relaxing with friends and colleagues.  Ample parking and great service with a nicely stocked convenience store right in the premises.

There is no shortage of taxis around the clock makes this place a gem for business travellers as well as families.  Free WiFi is provided all around the hotel with on-demand business services available upon request makes me come back here with each visit to Yangon.

Highly recommended for anyone planning a trip to Yangon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yanxin C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qc_hSEOVyYt90T8jEI1lbdGPaVqSrwdtGLOma43xF2tT-AGCQEDWJCQ3qq81gsm_HjiWg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed here for four nights. Location is a bit far from downtown but there is a local bustop nearby which cost just 200 kyats per ride. The hotel provides generator backups to Yangon’s daily power cuts so that’s great. There’s an emphasis on security in the form of an extra password-locked door at lift lobby, but to me that’s just a dash of inconvenience. The room is very well designed – I especially liked the direct usb ports provided. Killed a couple of mosquitoes in the room, and my hot water shower takes a couple minutes to heat up. Faint KTV music can be heard through room insulation on weekend nights. The hotel massage was just ok, not as good as I read. ||||Regarding the WiFi, they’re using the daily password system which I hate as it almost always gives me problems. Sure enough, my Wifi only works for the first night, after which I ditched using hotel WiFi since I’ve got my own mobile data. The staff were friendly with ready smiles and as a previous review points out, breakfast was outstanding. Absolutely loved the fried rice n ‘potato smiles’","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Co P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel location on Main Street Shwe Gone Daing. I returned to this one a couple times. The rooms are small-ish, the rates are average-ish, the service isn't bad and the staff, like most Burmese hotel staff in a reputable place they're just college students trying to do their best hoping to get a chance to leave the country or work for an NGO. Food was average for an Indian menu, I am sure it would have been better for local taste. Shwedagon Pagoda  is 15 mins drive from the hotel. Rooms are spacious , neat and stand at par with international standard.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I got myself a deluxe room on a high floor so my experience might be different from others. There was also no construction when I was there. My room is huge (and ceiling high), the television is so far away (8-10m) from my bed I have problem seeing the details. In contrast my hotel room in the city centre was so small that the TV is mounted like 80cm from the bed and they have to put it near the ceiling to increase the distance. The rooms are very well furnished (best value for money IMHO) and bigger than the family room that I had booked at the nearby Crystal Palace Hotel. It is a modern hotel with card entry. If you stay at the hotel you get a 20% discount at the Spa and the ONLY treatment I would recommend is the traditional massage at 10,000 kyat before discount. The Monalisa Restaurant (Level 1) is actually excellent and reasonably priced that I ended having dinner there every night. The breakfast is not excellent but quite good. There is actually an omelette counter so you can have you eggs done in any way but I did not see any eggs swimming in grease.||While the Wifi is not great, the signal is relatively strong and it is actually better than most hotels in Myanmar. Internet speed is not fast in the whole country and may break off.||Having stayed at various locations in Yangon, I can say this hotel is very centrally located. You can walk to visit Chauk Htat Gyi and Nga Htat Gyi Pagodas and be back within 2 hours without rushing. Shwedagon is also within walking distance.Downtown and Kandawgyi Lake are also not far away.  ||The best thing about this hotel is the hot water. You get very hot water very fast, better than some 5 star hotels.||Try not to venture to the basement as it is a "Love Tunnel" mostly for the local businessmen. The hotel staff is helpful, friendly and professional. Highly recommended, it is unbeatable at the price I paid. The only negative about this hotel is that there are no shops, shopping centres or amenities nearby. There is a diesel generator planted at the entrance of the hotel so any electrical outages are very short.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Good location near Myanmar Plaza.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Yankin on our first night in Myanmar - after a long travel (2 days from UK via HK) we were late getting in. Reception was dealt with quickly, and although the restaurant was closed, they found some beers for us, and allowed us to use the facilities to eat food which we obtained from nearby. Rooms were good, clean and well equipped. Breakfast was great, with omelettes cooked to order as well as the usual buffet fare. We travelled rounf Myanmar and returned to this hotel 2 weeks later to the same standard of service. Can't comment on the nearby ameneties, or the area in general as we were merely 'passing through' and needed a bed for the night. Overall, a good hotel with everything you need for a short stay. Probably not best location if you want a week here, but for us it was ideal. (We stayed in March, but Trip Advisor is playing up and keeps defaulting to todays date!)","Images":null,"When":""}]

Front Service/ 3 Stars - have to wait extra 35 min after 2 pm check-in time in order to get my room, no greeting when guests in or out. I have to greet good morning first.

Room/ 3 Stars - made a reservation with a confirmation of Premier room with king bed size in advance but they gave me twin joint bed, normally I won’t have any problem either King or twins Zipped bed however under the twin zipped bed, they placed normal sponge sheets which very hot and uncomfortable to sleep on. When I complained they said it was their standard.

Room Cleanliness/ 2 stars - a lot of previous guests hair (all type of hair) in under the floor and a lot of dust on the table. Extra pillow also very dirty, there was still on spot of stained on pillow, Look like a stained of human sperm.

When I called Front office staff and show him how bad the room was arranged, they finally switch with another but have to wait 3 more hours to be able to move to new room. Now room was not very different about cleaning, i was also stepped on a piece of glass which the housekeeper didn’t do their job well. Also still have hair on the floor for a newly clean room.

Breakfast/ 3 Stars - normal, not much choice.

Bellman - leaked of concentration. I was waiting for grab and when the grab arrived with another passengers, he opened the door for those passengers and when I was able to go in, he just closed the door. I was shocked for a second.

Hotel Location is Great which surrounding with restaurants.

Suggest: please train the housekeepers well, ohh need to train the supervisor first. [{"Name":"Meikhtilar Steel Structure","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV40oqjASaBkvTUjHhtYIX53dyr84vL5Wtn9ZvYr9j7aNk2HQs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unpleasant Experience, Misleading Policies

I recently stayed at this hotel and had a highly disappointing experience. When I booked a double bed room, I assumed it would accommodate my family, including my two children. To my dismay, upon arrival, I was informed that the hotel's policy only allowed one child in a double room without extra charges.

Not only was this policy not clearly stated during the booking process, but I also had to pay additional fees for my second child, making the stay much more expensive than anticipated. This felt like a blatant attempt to squeeze more money out of guests, and I found it completely unacceptable.

Furthermore, when I tried to discuss this issue with the staff, they were unhelpful and dismissive, showing a lack of empathy towards my situation. The lack of transparency and the way I was treated left a bitter taste in my mouth.

I would strongly advise potential guests to thoroughly review the hotel's policies before booking, as this experience has left me feeling deceived and dissatisfied. I will not be returning to this hotel in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sai Htun Htun Oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUtIcSSlih268kO5CMKZquOQ7NxsUSK16LRUUBWjDPu1yRWGat=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"2 Stars hotel. user_reviews: [{"Name":"Nick N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The desk staff was awesome!!  They were very helpful and spoke a good bit of English.  The upscale home turned hotel, looked tired and in need of repair.  But there was a lot of very nice woodwork all around and the hotel had \"character,\" for sure! ||||I personally enjoyed sitting out by a small balcony reading and watching the birds.  ||||They had a free breakfast in another next door restaurant which four breakfast options.  The breakfast was very good, and the waiters/waitresses were very friendly and helpful.  We had three of the four breakfast options and they were all good.||||Here was one of the meals:   Steamed Dimsum, fried noodles, chicken sausage,  sliced Honey Dew and Papaya with something on it that tastes like a perfume smells but is really good with coffee and Oolong tea.  Oh,  and some  kind of  a fish meat based hot sauce...also good.||||From the airport to the hotel we got a taxi from the taxi desk inside for 6,000 MMK but going back we found a taxi that only charged us 4,000 MMK.||||It was a nice place to stay on a budget!!  I would stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ukairo_dash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcnOWm00_8Vg0_qD09-e04s-i2bb5F6bVsdwxSboR_yrT1yPvciwzMvgtJ8p5a3bvmZzg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed at the Excel Palace for 4 nights of a month long stay in Yangon. So in an apples-to-apples comparison, it is close to 3 stars. . .  but falls short in several ways. You be the judge:||The room was large and wasnt lacking for furniture, but the drapes were badly torn and the bedding had a lot of visible stains.  ||The plush headboard was likewise filthy and the pillows were very well used.||Moving on to the bathroom, the shower had plenty of hot water but 75% flowed out if the downspout, leaving the shower with rather weak pressure. The shower head was mounted below chest level. I brought these issues up with the staff on day 1, but there was no change during our time there.||Finally, the free breakfast. It was next door in a busy restaurant. There is a choice of 4 set menus with no changes allowed (it is not a buffet). Most hotels (every one we have stayed at in Yangon) have a buffet. The restaurant wouldn't even give us water, only tea or coffee (which I doubt is from filtered water). The water at the hotel is turbid (a light brown color), and I imagine that is what you get with the tea/coffee.||We brought our own bottled every morning which was not a problem.||I would give details about the number of flies in the restaurant, but suffice it to say that if you dont like flies buzzing everywhere, you might want to avoid the place.||The location (walking distance to the lake) was ok. A longer walk to other restaurants (with the exception of a Thai restaurant just across the street which was excellent).||All in all, I'd like to give it 3 stars. The house is nice. They could quickly fix most issues. But it seems the management is not of a mind to follow through.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Hotels in Yangon, now that Myanmar is the \"flavour of the month\", are now very expensive with the xception of the Excel Palace. It is not downtown but close to Inya Lake and the Inya Lake Hotel which is where I wanted to be close to.||It is an old private home and has no lift but spiral staircases, so be warned.||My room was large with two twin beds. All shampoos, soap etc were all supplied, as was free water every day. There is a safe in the room. The WiFi worked well.||There is also a well stocked bar fridge and the beer price was cheaper than buying outside!||The reception staff could not be more helpful...nothing was too much trouble.||The included breakfast is not in the Hotel but just around the corner in a restaurant.||The service there was a mixture of very good, when the waitresses were working our table but a bit hit and miss when it was waiters!!||Taxis are everywhere and very cheap so it is easy to get to anywhere you want to go with no problems.||Would I stay there again...you bet I would...very happily.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We only arrived at 4pm and left at 5am the following morning but the service and assistance we received from the front desk was outstanding. We needed a bus booked the following morning and that was no problem – they also had the taxi ready for us at 5am the following morning before we even got down to reception. The room itself was so big (but a refreshing change from some others), that it had two air conditioners. We were on the top floor – if you have an irrational fear of pigeons, maybe request a room on a lower floor, as we had a few scratching around on the roof, not enough to wake us up though.||||We didn’t get to try breakfast before we left. There are a few decent looking restaurants right near the hotel although we didn’t get a chance to try them either. The Excel Palace is in walking distance to Inya Lake and only a short drive to Shwedagon. Unless you want to be in walking distance of Sule Paya and Bogyoke Markets, I’d recommend this place purely for the service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kayk44","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdGDJ6WBs5CBoNVcQAwShh25kntoFa0rN3szxhkmmJHnXagNPuSfO1BRpzbnKc5wyCe_g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Excel Palace Hotel for 22 days.  First and foremost, we mention our #1 staff.  Simon, the manager, and also the assistant manager who went out of their way to assist us.  From city directions, room comfort, even impromptu language lessons, they were there with a smile.  Our room was comfortable, clean and quiet.  The location of the hotel, just off New University Avenue, allowed for peaceful nights, no traffic noise at all.  There are good restaurants nearby and downtown is just a short taxi ride away.  We will certainly return to Excel Palace when returning to Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"neamman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeiIm6t64oXJwlfKKV-SU2ENLb40SwZCvBWRts5o7WimonLggB5R8bs4qOdTbCTDXjyRQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"An old converted house which provided what I expected for the price paid. The staff in the hotel lobby (including the doormen) and also all of security at the front of the hotel are so friendly and welcoming. The duty manager (Nyein) is one of the best I have seen in the hotels I've been to worldwide because she really cares about the hotel guests and checks in with you and you're well-being. She helped with putting an ironing board and an iron for the room which was a really nice addition that I needed. When there was a slight misunderstanding (which was quickly and promptly rectified), she made sure to fix the issue with assorted fruits, juice and a complimentary meal that came with dessert, which she personally arranged and brought to the room. The women at the reception were amazingly friendly and welcoming everytime I went up and down to the room. The food is exceptional, the staff should be applauded and the swimming pool.....fantastic! The hotel’s centralized aircon is not working. They have installed portable aircon which is very noisy. And the room is not cool enough and quite warm. This make the stay in the room was terrible. However, the staff are very friendly and helpful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AjithEngland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Arrived at 2am in the morning. Staff were friendly and helpful. Didn't realise how big the hotel was when booked but didn't make a difference. Room was clean and spacious. Liked the fact that if you needed a taxi they used an uber type service which told them the price which they told you  and then they told the driver. Always cheaper than the return trip. We were having trouble booking tables at restaurants and internal flights to Bagan, Mandlay and Isle Inlay. Concierge sorted it all out for us. Excellent service for us. So would definitely recommend.|Ps the pool is great two !!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cool Papa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsqSz7h--lod5g6JTqopBJ1B9VJWGmIvRoNiWj7AQwn1oG1T99=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This has all, or at least most, of the earmarks of a grand hotel, but circumstances and events have made the situation not so great.

First, the positives: the predominantly young staff are kind, polite, well-trained, and eager to serve. This is refreshing.

The hotel has Grand rooms, beautifully appointed. In fact the entire hotel is beautifully decorated with expensive interior design, plush furniture , deeply padded carpeting and expensive fittings.

My room is beautifully decorated with quality linens, a great mattress, and comfortable traditional- style furniture. The bathroom looks brand-new with high-end rain shower, good plumbing, and tile work and fittings which befit a five-star hotel.

The water pressure was always strong and the temperature never varied.

The price for the room is a great value at approximately 50 US dollars in May of 2023.

I have slept well here during my three night stay.

Unfortunately, the hotel does not have high occupancy and had a very empty feeling when I checked in. Partly because it's the low season and very hot. But also tourists are absent because of the political situation in Myanmar.

A military coup has caused great instability and there is fighting raging throughout the country, although Rangoon itself seems free of violence.

So there is only The Veranda bar restaurant open for drinks and dining and I have only seen one other hotel guest when I went there.

The ATM was out of order when I went to use it. Other services the hotel used to offer are no longer available due to the lack of guests, and certain floors of the hotel have apparently been sealed closed.

The district surrounding the hotel did not seem safe to walk at night and this was confirmed to me by hotel staff.

The breakfast buffet is just so so, and not of a wide variety. However there are delicious jams, yoghurts, and The Omelette station provides nice tasty omelettes. Coffee is very good.

I feel bad to point out the negatives, many of which are out of control of the hotel due to the circumstances of the country.

You'll need to download grab onto your phone in order to use taxi service because there's no public transit readily available.

Although I really like this hotel, during my next visit I'll probably stay in an area which is conducive to walking to explore cafes shopping and nightlife.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPgAi_sltOuTTPVl0wUhz2P1x3HhD5xipclMTg&fid=0x0:0x4ffd61fdf8d14432"],"When":"2023-5-10"},{"Name":"zinmin smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPw0AzUzCpsmxnkCBA6MJCZ8Z31j5s-dlNeFEvMSxXANZKVsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I stayed two nights in the Rose Garden  Hotel and  I love it, These hotels are so luxurious. Locations are easy to go anywhere and they also have a little garden behind the hotel. And you will feel free and so relaxing cause they have many plants, big trees and pools .
And one thing that I didn't like is the air-con system. They put a moveable mini air con in every room, their main air system is working  for slow Fan. But I really love this hotel and should try to be here.👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3qJqzh1v1NQX6B4Vxnfx18XMrorR0CJ4oZHo&fid=0x0:0x4ffd61fdf8d14432"],"When":"2023-6-18"}]

Definitely coming back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dicey E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Found a hotel in Yangon that suits my quirky sensibility to a “T” – the Hotel Yno in the Tamwee section of the city. ||I’ve tried a few lodging venues around Yangon this last year. For 5 years I used to frequent Fame Hotel on Po Sein Road near scenic Kandawgyi Lake, though this last year management remodeled the rooms making them about half the size they were and raised the room rates.  ||A couple of times I stayed at Uptown Hotel due to its proximity to the Bowling Alley across the thoroughfare; but after the crippling bowling workout my ancient body suffered two months ago I stopped bowling; no more for me. ||Six years ago a rented a pleasant house in the Tamwee area of Yangon and thoroughly enjoyed the neighborhood so I checked on line for hotels situated in those environs. Saw the ad for Hotel Yno and decided to give it a shot. ||First off it’s more economical than Fame or Uptown by a few bucks – half the price of Uptown for more or less the same quality room and so-called complimentary breakfast. But for me it location is superb; within a short walking distance to a cinema, two supermarkets, a bustling outdoor, farmers’ market and at least two halfway decent disco-nightspots for entertainment and possibly companionship. ||The rooms aren’t palatial though not cramped either and have all the amenities travelers look for: speedy wifi, cable TV and hot water shower. The staff is particularly affable and helpful. ||I travel from where I work in Taunggyi to Yangon every two months, I glad I stumbled upon Hotel Yno it is now the place for me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location and neighborhood is not great. I don't know why many people are giving them such high ratings. Maybe they got lucky or they have never stayed in a hotel that offers these services. The driver is always chewing on something ghastly and spit quite often, horrible. For such a good hotel has anyone seen the bed sheets, maybe one should before even sitting on it. Maybe people who are giving such good reviews are used to sleep on dirty beds. Anyway to cut the talk short, watch what you eat and don't be a fool.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dinesh kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_GuDRTv1WgjN1nG59cJbQ5XBwhgOcvyBTy3ErbwqA6oUWZWG3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New review 2019:

The hotel has been upgraded with the same excellent service as before. The rooms are clean and maintained well. They even have an ATM in the lobby. There is a 24hour CityMart (local supermarket) nearby. Since the hotel is on the main road, you can easily get Grab (like Uber car sharing service) and go around the city.

Do read my previous review below:

*****************************
Old review from 2017 below:

We stayed in the hotel for 3 nights in the Superior twin room and 2 nights in the Junior Suite B with Bathtub. As most of the reviews have already mentioned,  choose the rooms towards the back of the hotel (away from the road) and preferably to the right (facing east), these rooms have a better view and also you will get a glimpse of the rising sun. The hotel's buffet breakfast is great and each day they have a special local cuisine. This, in my opinion, would be a very safe way to try out the local dishes. The staff can speak English and are very friendly. The rooms are clean and we'll  maintained. The only problem is  that the doors do not appear to be sound proof and could be a problem if there are a lot of guests moving in-and-out of their rooms. TIP: There is a City Mart outlet straight down the road, about 15mins walk. There is a hospital nearby. There are some great food places in about 15mins walk.  (Note: photos are from the Junior Suite B room #403)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTRys335Gz8GYnI6YYBqGeugAo2Gk_wDNJK7Uv&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-1-7"},{"Name":"Sandy’s Shine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd9XwYaXMx0VXxehGbmy_BXGG7o4D1R7qOLglJAXom2nLJ9IM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best technology in the leather industry","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Borja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNLX_Fs9Bq4tJkkoiCk_V6a2wYuYVowqo_cuP2tYcQNCXRug1DBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small hotel of about 20 rooms. They do have good bed sheets, nice cozy room, very clean toilet and bathroom, and their towels are nice too.

They also have a simple buffet breakfast but would surely be filling. They have the normal fried rice, noodles, veggies, fishball, mominga, congee, bread, coffee & tea, different spreads, cereal, juice and fruits.

All staff, including the owner James, are very friendly  and they will make sure you will have the best stay.

Downside is location is in a main highway, but the noise is bearable. It is located a bit far from downtown area. Cab fare though is very inexpensive in Myanmar especially if you use Grab. If you let the front desk of the hotel book your Grab ride, you will even get a.discount.

Definitely this is a value for money hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"陳適恆","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9Qa9YgyEIj_SG6Dkjal_b0smqbVY9X9C36qkb8MzTlsHDqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of the best hotel I have ever stay in my life. If I have a chance to visit Yongon, I'll stay in this hotel again~","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leo Tao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyLsqEdu89TiHXshavWfuGzBbJw49JdOuwO4AnF4J32_TMs8Dq1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Air con and Hot water is good, didn't try wifi, Bed is clean, soft and no smell, have lift and price start from $35, breakfast are just so so","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTt64iNuxauvH55Cx-DcSXsdO6eos2YCKWqVBM&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-4-2"},{"Name":"Anja Kroll","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7REscpP0ZTDKbjkwiA5gr5PBXebQvWd02TlbpuCIbZF3bUUVT6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice rooms, good food, driver service, very friendly, overall good experience","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Sky Star Hotel
address: No. 51/B, Sky Star Hotel, 1 E Horse Race Course Rd, Yangon 11211
descriptions: Warm rooms & suites in an informal hotel with a restaurant & a bar, plus an outdoor pool & a spa.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Javier Sona","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQnUd27AKg9svga9_QET4x2Sxq9FHmO9iXd1BsfC-x9wK75Dqx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Review of My Stay

I travel quite a lot, and I have to say it’s been a long time since I’ve encountered such pleasant people. They make you feel at home, always with a smile and ready to help. The staff is outstanding.

The Location: The cleanliness is exquisite, the rooms are bright, new, and have a modern style with great design. The beds are super comfortable, and when you close the curtains, it’s completely dark, allowing for ideal rest. The rooms are spacious and tidy, with a practical and clean bathroom, and a large wardrobe for storing clothes. The security is excellent, and the atmosphere is pleasant and tranquil, featuring pools on the terrace.

Food: The dining is excellent and very reasonably priced.

I’m genuinely surprised because I’ve tried to find a flaw but haven’t been able to.

Before this hotel, I stayed at a typical resort where the crowds, noise, and activities overwhelm any sense of tranquility. Upon arriving here, I quickly felt at home, relaxed, and thoroughly enjoyed the experience.

It’s a pleasure to be in a hotel that combines the warmth of a cozy establishment with the comfort and decor of a high-end hotel.

I highly recommend it. I can’t express enough gratitude to the staff and the manager, who treats guests with enthusiasm and warmth, paying close attention to every detail.

In short: warmth, comfort, cleanliness, incredible infrastructure, magnificent service, and a tranquil environment—100% recommendable. This is undoubtedly an experience I won’t forget and hope to repeat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"SOE HTET","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWla-Ejww2zw_KCGErgsdgiUOsBpNjlzrMuMerAJwsP_Y-oSams=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sky Star Hotel in Yangon exceeded my expectations! The rooftop pool provided stunning views of the city, making it a perfect spot to relax after a day of sightseeing. Conveniently located, it was easy to explore nearby attractions. The staff greet you with huge helpful smiles and are indeed friendly and welcoming. The room was clean and comfortable, however there was a musty smell to the room. Perhaps the result of  past smoking in the room?  Decor wise the whole place is dated and makes me feel like I've stepped into a 90's film actually some parts resembled the Titanic! I kinda liked that but whatever floats your boat I guess! I can deal with it for a night. I was super happy with the gym, which was clean and well equipt. The pool area is nice but looks a bit like an oasis in a desert. There is huge space around the pool that is used for functions. My purpose for booking this hotel was for the use of the gym and pool before a late night flight the day after. I wanted to spend my last day chilling by the pool but there was indeed a poolside funtion, which meant the pool was closed. I explained my purpose for booking to the manager and he was understanding and allowed me to swim while the staff were preping the event. I am very pleased with his understanding of this situation. Though still slightly frustrated that I could'nt spend my last day by the pool. Instead I reclined in true 90's style overlooking the roof tops of Yangon on my dusty balcony and took full advantage of the 1pm late check out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marissa C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is pretty great. Pools is fun and nice.||The only exception was the room was in need of a little tlc.  Wall paper was just starting to peel and a little bit of mold around the A/C unit.||other than that it's a very nice hotel.||There is not much around if you like to walk around.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ko Pauk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUOCsxZ3_Jdk6ms5EJ9O-ozAEJWBZXJn6a0EFTsP4gTQ8WaJORvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As for me, it's the worst hotel I've ever experienced. Then I received a call from room service, I said I want wine. If they responded not available, I would be totally fine. But what they did is they talk each other (fortunately or unfortunately, I heard over phone), one of them blame the one who answer the call why he didn't said it's not available. The amenities seem good but not really. Conditioner bottle has broken, water tap is broken, towels are really bad smell.

Next morning, breakfast time, ordering omelette made me disappointed from the cook.

I recommend not to go this hotel. Please email me for more info.

title: Asian Smile Hotel
address: No. 324, Thanthumar Road, Thuwanna, Yangon 11072
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brandon Rudd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3BEm67ErtBvBTnTEY_JdnDPNZmcEPQkFQ8FQpZRsN2KeORA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing place to stay if you really want to get lost in Myanmar! The staff are super kind and helpful, alongside being quite amusing at times.

They may not speak much English but they more than make up for it with service, not to mention they are very generous. A person here let me borrow some flip flops for the time I went to pagoda and helped me dress in their traditional outfit. Thanks to them I have a great experience in the country.

The location is pretty convenient too if you use the grab app, you can book a taxi and take a ride to downtown in about 10 minutes.

The room also has all the basic necessities and even come with free body wash and shampoo incase you run out as well as toothbrush.

The power may go out a few times but thats not their fault, its the countries power grid with rolling blackouts and they try to keep the power going with a generator I believe. The hot water in the shower is a little short but with how hot the country is it didn't bother me.

Hopefully they see this so thank you Asian Smile Hotel!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Myint oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOmactE_SsuEBl2unndIH-zfOLgexF7ZWcsQAWzZo2mqLLULTKcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Wide and clean room. title: Hotel Bond
address: 49 Hledan Street, Yangon
descriptions: Unfussy quarters, some with balconies, in an unassuming hotel offering a cafe & free Wi-Fi.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"A budget hotel with very friendly and helpful staff, offering a good breakfast with a buffet. Note that the rooms have a shared bathroom, which should be taken into account. The internet connection can occasionally be interrupted, so it’s better to have your own SIM card for work","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Ortiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWq-BNP10zsikF7cEz4hQxZ-OBwASD31FTupiRHyjoAXQoc0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"At first it looks like a very good deal, a whole apartment with 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms for a low price.  When you see how dirty it is then the price makes sense.

But, you are given 2 doorlocks for the two bedroons, there is no doorlock to the main living room.  At firsr it seemed like just a strange inconvenience because they are "changing locks" but in hindsight I think this is just a socially acceptable excuse but in hindsight I believe it to be deception (based on their behavior of just entering the room when they feel like it.

The first time my wife was surprised and they were blessed by getting to see to much of her.  After that they kept coming back again and again under the guise of being extra helpful.

Their behavior was polite but I found it completely unacceptable.  At night I  dragged the couch in front of the door and put another chair on top of it and leaned against the door so that if someone tried to push the door opened then the chair should fall off and make a loud noise and alert me that someone was trying to enter the room at night.  At 11am exactly I heard the staff in the room.  They had come in to clean the room (without calling first) an hour before checkout time.

When I went out I saw how he had quietly and carefully wedge the door open already expecting that there was such a trap; showing that he had developed this skill over time and that he was aware that he was sneaking in instead of calling.

I was enraged!  I come from Texas where the law says that if someone did this at either my home OR A HOTEL that I would have the legal right to kill them.

I know that Myanmar law does not allow that and I respect Myanmar law; however they need to realize that they are authorized for foreign customers and they should try to give reasonable respect that when we are paying to sleep in a place that we have a right to privacy.

I cannot consider this hotel to be safe as you are not entitled to security of a safe space.

I have talked to Myanmar friends and this behavior is also not acceptable by their own culture.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Smokers room and unable to sleep in room, called the reception they offered air freshener when I had booked a non-smoking room. There are a lot of street food around this area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I didn't have high hopes for this hotel, but the photos and rating seemed good.  I should have been more cautious and read the reviews more carefully.  First, there is no elevator.  My fault for not checking that, so no negative rating for this.  The hotel has 8 floors so you may have to climb 8 stories to your room. The biggest shock factor was how old and beat up the rooms were.  The website pictures look nice but are either photoshopped or so old that they no longer are accurate.  The walls are dirty and covered in the blood of many dead mosquitoes.  The bathrooms used to have white grout, but now are black with mildew.  -2 rating for horribly accurate pictures.  Second, the hotel does nothing for mosquito control.  I stayed in multiple hotels throughout Myanmar and every hotel was proactive at controlling the mosquitoes.  This place does nothing and the rooms were filled with them.  We got bit multiple times during the night.  -1 rating for mosquito control.  We got the entire floor (two rooms), and one of the rooms smelled of cigarette smoke.  -1 rating for that.  +1 rating as the staff seemed nice, the breakfast was decent, and location was good.  That adds up to a +2 rating.  I would not recommend this place at all.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Coming from Siem Reap it took my brain a little bit to adjust to a new economy! The first hotel I booked at $20 per night was an absolute dive. I got out of there as quickly as I could! Walked into Hotel Bond having checked it out online, yes it was a higher price, but worth every penny. The staff were so welcoming when I turned up at 8 in the morning, got me settled into a room and even invited me to have breakfast. The staff carried my suitcase up the stairs and even with the shared bathroom, i never saw the other guest sharing the bathroom so there was no conflict there. The bathroom was excellent with a rainforest shower and a smaller shower head. My suggestions here would be to get some bigger shampoo and shower gel bottles, the tiny individual ones are a waste of plastic and in this case space given that it is a shared bathroom. Putting some floor mats for the bathroom would also be a good idea, 2-3 so each room can have their own.||The room was small but very comfortable and clean.||The breakfast was decent and the daily noodle dish was always vegetable only which is just perfect!||My only other recommendation would be large water refills. Whilst having large water bottles as well as small is a big step above most hotels, I would prefer to use no plastic at all. When I asked the guy at the desk where I might refill my bottle, he said he didn't know and to maybe try a pagoda, when I walked out the door it was less than 30 seconds before I saw that there are water tanks on the street all over the place and these are for anyone to use! Hurrah! Still it would be great if the hotel included water refills in their breakfast room.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel H Valley Yangon
address: 24 Shwe Gon Taing Street 3, Yangon
descriptions: Cosy rooms & suites in a laid-back hotel offering a bar, a restaurant & a cafe, plus free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ye Linn Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZoaCe4c9RPsb86zp6LF15u3dKGeMIQ9TEi8FCYnu80I2P2Nqfkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Modern Comfort in the Heart of Yangon

Looking for contemporary style and amenities in the center of historic Yangon? Look no further than the H Valley Hotel. This modern hotel boasts sleek rooms, first-rate service, and a prime location to experience all that Yangon offers.

From the moment I walked into the lobby, I was impressed by the chic, minimalist decor. Rooms follow the same aesthetic with floor-to-ceiling windows, plush white linens, and a muted gray and teal color scheme. Touches like rainfall showers, free Wi-Fi, and city views from my room made it an urban oasis. I loved starting mornings with the lavish breakfast buffet.

But what I appreciated most was the excellent service. The friendly staff went above and beyond, arranging tours, transportation, dining reservations, and airport transfers seamlessly. Their attention to detail embodies Asian hospitality.

For visitors who crave modern amenities without sacrificing an authentic cultural experience, H Valley is a perfect home base. This polished hotel lets you indulge in 21st-century comforts while exploring one of Asia’s most mesmerizing cities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Set on a side street, 10 minutes walk from Shwedagon Pagoda. title: Serviced Residence by 85 SOHO @ Upper Pansodan
address: 137 Upper Pansodan Rd, Yangon 11222
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Neel Kolhatker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWC34GJxIxDd3frYMYXHJtK-cZDZwVBPEfP5BDWnBb7rZgJg8of1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This was my second time staying in this place. Compared to ten months ago, the apartments have gotten a lot of wear and tear. Little things aren't working like the AC remote, the door lock was missing batteries, the water heater switch was gone. You can tell the unit isn't cleaned completely. This apt building is still pretty new but it's already gone downhill. I can imagine in a year or two it will be in really bad condition.

Another thing is that when I tried to check in they claimed I paid too low a rate on Agoda so they would not honor my reservation. They said they had told Agoda but I never received any cancellation. It's completely wrong to force guests to come to your hotel and then tell them they cannot check in. They cld have cancelled my booking or at least sent a message thru Agoda. After an hour of waiting Agoda finally agreed to cover the price difference but I wldn't trust booking this place as they don't seem to know what they are doing with online bookings. If they want 40usd or more a night for this place I don't think it's good value as you can get a 4 star hotel for that much in Yangon.

Other than these issues, it's in a good location, there are two small shops downstairs to buy water and a couple restaurants I didn't try. It's in a development of many new apt buildings but most are unoccupied. You can walk to a nearby mall, huge park, or South to the central area or it's a $1 Grab ride.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yuki San","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzwG8uqoG2shcIbp8euWoWF7RD2Z9ltaS53e0xPOIFTlobcZM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"do not book this property on agoda. they do not honour their prices on agoda and will ask you for a higher rate. avoid at all costs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mohana krishna Ponna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsfs7PTn-kNb0eo76riEUm6DjD5JQQc9kh8SEJjYT6E5smRJ8Idw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best service apartment

Situated in a prime location, this hotel offers not only a convenient base for exploration but also stunning vistas of the river and the iconic Shwedagon Pagoda.

The strategic location of Hotel Grand Vista is a standout feature. Positioned in the heart of Ahlon Township, guests have easy access to key attractions, shopping centers, and cultural sites. The proximity to the river adds an extra layer of charm, providing guests with picturesque scenes and a tranquil ambiance that feels like a retreat within the city.

The highlight of this hotel is undoubtedly the panoramic views it offers. Rooms and common areas are strategically designed to showcase the beauty of the Yangon River and the majestic Shwedagon Pagoda. Witnessing the sunrise or sunset against these iconic landmarks from the comfort of your room is an experience that adds unparalleled value to your stay.

The accommodations at Hotel Grand Vista are a testament to comfort and sophistication. Well-appointed rooms with modern amenities ensure a relaxing retreat after a day of exploration. The blend of contemporary design and local influences creates a unique atmosphere that reflects the rich cultural tapestry of Myanmar.

Service at Hotel Grand Vista is characterized by warmth and efficiency. The staff's dedication to ensuring a seamless experience for guests is evident in every interaction. From the moment of check-in to personalized assistance throughout the stay, the hospitality reflects a commitment to guest satisfaction.

The on-site dining options contribute to the overall allure of the hotel. Whether indulging in local delicacies or savoring international cuisine, guests are treated to a culinary journey that caters to diverse tastes. The restaurant's ambiance, coupled with impeccable service, enhances the dining experience.

In conclusion, Hotel Grand Vista in Ahlon Township, Yangon, is a captivating blend of convenience, luxury, and awe-inspiring views. Whether you're a traveler exploring the city or a business professional seeking a comfortable retreat, this hotel exceeds expectations, providing an unforgettable stay characterized by exceptional service and breathtaking panoramas.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aung Pyae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiII0Syf3nSXA5B3SZ3DHTG5mxV308k2zHkuer_eIu5EltUaE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"indoor swimming pool open till 7 pm.

We needed a place in central Yangon for the night of our arrival in Myanmar, knowing we were moving on the next day. We wanted it to be reasonably priced and capable of accommodating my family of 4 in one room.  To our surprise, this hotel was quite nice. It's on a quiet street, and our top floor room was huge. The restaurant was good for dinner, and the breakfast was adequate.  The bathroom could use a thorough cleaning, however. We booked on agoda and had no problem.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Denis K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed in a superior room which cost me 85 USD per night including buffet breakfast. This is a mid-range hotel on Yangon’s scale of things. The staff is very nice and attentive to guests, always smiling and on hand to help with requests and enquiries. My room was clean and tidy, it had an AC and a king size bed with clean linen and comfortable pillows. There were a tele and a minibar in the room as well. The bathroom had both a bath and a shower. The room would be cleaned every day, toiletries and linen on the bed replaced. A diverse buffet breakfast was served every morning: there was a big board with Asian breakfast choices as well as a small table with fried eggs, toasts and coffee. It was definitely worth the money I paid. Hotels in Yangon are expensive, sometimes you pay more than you would in London, therefore Holiday was a good find. ||||A couple of cons: ||1 - Sound insulation is poor, you would head other guests returning at night. If you have sleeping problems, consider the noise factor. ||2 – The hotel does not accept US dollars if they do not look perfectly mint. I would not put it as criticism of the hotel though. You will not be able to pay with USD’s of bad condition anywhere in Myanmar. Lake at the end of Phoe Sein Road is a pleasant outing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amini K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed for nearly a night at the Holiday Hotel in Yangon, Myanmar in May 2014. On our way from Hanoi to Bagan, we had to spend a night here before catching our plane to Bagan the next day. Upon arriving in Yangon, the hotel does not offer transportation from the airport so we took a taxi for about $10 USD. The hotel is about 20 minutes from the airport. Staff was friendly as the hotel is family owned. Since we left very early the next morning (around 4am) we were not able to experience the breakfast but complimentary water in the room was nice. Rooms are a bit small but clean and with A/C and TV. Elevator functions well. The rooms are otherwise basic. We found the price of hotels in Yangon expensive (over $100) but in our case we didn't have too much of a choice unless we slept at the airport. All in all, Holiday Hotel met our needs for a short sleep.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jake M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Great location by the airport. The lobby was really warm, because they don't run the a/c in there. It's only a problem if you're using the wifi which you have to be in there to get signal. When it's nice outside or it rains, the lobby feels amazing because they open up the doors, making it a nice breeze-way. The breakfast buffet is delicious. title: Alfa Hotel
address: Alfa Hotel No. 41, Yawmingyi Qr., Nawaday Road, Yangon
descriptions: Unassuming hotel offering an Asian restaurant & a cafe/bar, plus warm, traditional rooms.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Simon T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Review is for the Sapphire Bar on top of the Alpha Hotel. The hotel looks like a 3 star hotel and we had some doubts when we went into the hotel lounge. Reaching the bar on top of level 12, we were greeted by a rather bare large rooftop with chairs and tables placed loosely. The bar is literally two simple tables with different alcohol bottles displayed on it. We didn't have much hope. But the view was great and we had a good view of the padoga and full moon, which was really nice. Ordered a mojito and it was not bad at all. In other countries, this will probably get two or three stars from me but given that it is in myanmar, I think the place deserves 4 stars. Just remember that this is still a relatively new emerging market and places are still not fully commercialize yet, which is the main point. Sit back, enjoy the view, sip the cocktail which is only usd2.5, and relax. I'm sure one day, this bar will go through dramatic transformation into a high end bar with proper chairs, deco and expensive cocktails but I truly like it the way it is now. Enjoy while it lasts.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donn Emmanuelle Quines","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkeEqSIQhYXlRK9H5QLDluZQhC-xQO3HMf0Q7j9u-lLhtjgpo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want a decent view of Yangon, this is the right place. The Sapphire Lounge that sits on top of the hotel serves as their rooftop bar. Great place for unwinding. The main downside is the set-up, expect to see rusty tables and chairs. Not the typical rooftop bar setting. They also have free WiFi connection and its pretty good and stable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"MT0024","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I did not stay here.  I did, however, visit the rooftop bar and highly recommend it.  You don't need to be a guest of the hotel to visit the rooftop.  Simply go to the lobby and tell the staff you'd like to go to the rooftop and they will show you the elevator.  When you get to the roof, you will inevitably see a quiet place with few patrons and several attentive servers.  You will have a great view of Shwedagon Pagoda and all of downtown Yangon.  The place isn't really glitzy but it has a definite charm, perhaps as a recognition of quieter times in Yangon.  It is a must visit in Yangon.  Prices for drinks are only marginally higher than in shops on the street and certainly much, much lower than more trendy rooftops in the city.  Visit for a taste of bygone Asia!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ruti K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I'll start by saying we aren't very demanding customers. In nearly 3 weeks in myanmar we stayed in various places, all of which we found great, even very cheap backpackers hostels with no warm water or mirror in the room. However, we do think you should get what you pay for and this place just doesn't make sense. ||positive things first: the hotel is well located, near some nice restaurants and cafes and not far from the shwedagon pagoda. And the wifi works well. ||Other than that, it really sucked. Was by far and away the worst hotel we stayed in, in an almost 3 week trip to Myanmar - and the most expensive!! (Slightly surpassing even a beach front bungalow at Ngapali!)||The hotel and its furniture and equipment are very very old with some ridiculous features, like none of the room or bathroom lights working unless the main light is on (which makes it hard when one person is awake and the other isn't), and an almost cute built- in radio set from the 70s at the very latest! ||bad smell in the room (of smoking, to which a bellboy was sent to spray some anti-odor all over the room...) and in the hallways (of ginger cooking or something like that) - both topped with a lingering scent of mold. Bath was uninviting to say the least. ||My friend came in late and accidentally  walked into a different room to discover that the key worked!! After which she tried a few more and apparently the magic key opened all the rooms she tried. Didn't really matter because the hotel was empty except for us - and rightfully so.||The reason we picked this hotel was because of the so-called rooftop bar, which turned out to be a poor guy standing in front of a small reception table stocked with some alcohol bottles,  and an entirely unimpressive view. Yes, you can see the Shwedagon pagoda but aside from that not much more. ||We know there is a supply-demand problem in Yangon which makes for a situation in which hotels don't need to try very hard and still have a steady flow of clients. However, this place was hostel-level with hotel price so better to just stay at a very basic backpackers place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Brigg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLhdIWW96MVAYNwwgC6TctxJC4WBThP9-N1OaJHUEYzZ-lNLA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The hotel has an air of faded elegance. The single lift stops between every second floor so there is a walk down or up to your floor.

The Sapphire Club is the bar on the rooftop. To get there you take the lift to the top then go up a half floor to get to 12. Then you have to walk down a corridor between guest rooms to get to the stairs to the top.

Though the decor is basic the bar is friendly with very good White Russian and Mojito cocktails at very reasonable prices. title: Hotel Accord
address: No. 69 Damar Yone Street, Myay Ni Gone, Yangon 11111
descriptions: Simple rooms & suites in a casual hotel offering an airy restaurant & free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Myo Thet Kyu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqTMMPEWmJ_ABi8T-HDgXv57cXEFzvKmnHX-TvAVRICPeniuc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"just checked-in. although location is good, the room is dirty. But the bedsheets he brought still gots some stains on it. I friendly told him may be the laundry service place is not working properly.. still the housekeeper resists that the laundry service they used is used by most of the famous hotels in town. The second time, the room (206) was at least a meter wider, had two bedside tables, and easy to reach plugs, which made all the difference! Another tiny complaint is that they offer water bottles but no easy-access to a more eco-friendly water refill station, but I asked the staff at the kitchen to help me and that always obliged (albeit with discomfort on their faces). Let’s do our part to use less single-use plastics!!

title: The Loft Hotel
address: Yangon, 33, Yaw Min Gyi Street, Dagon Township The Loft Hotel
descriptions: Sleek accommodations in a hip hotel offering a restaurant with a patio & bar, plus a garden & cafe.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tibor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4OOWobe8XluLdExxIo6NECTMqOXhOwdhdHXRX6tNrGhxnyOHC2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stayed at The Loft Hotel in Yangon, and it was an excellent choice. The hotel is located on a smaller side street, so it was wonderfully quiet, even at night. Everything was spotless, and the staff were incredibly attentive—they answered all my questions and helped with everything I needed. The beds were extremely comfortable, making it easy to rest after a long day. The breakfast was delicious, and the location couldn’t be better. Downtown and the main attractions were all within walking distance, including the Bogyoke Market, which is just 400 meters away. In the evening, I recommend checking out T.H.O.R, a lively live music venue with a stage, only about a 5-minute walk from the hotel. I’ll definitely stay here again next time I’m in Yangon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiCgMTlH089BM19hN6wcRJBVYor7V0jLS22K9R&fid=0x0:0xced1b2e2a3e9c6f6"],"When":"2025-1-26"},{"Name":"Janu-Rey Sebastian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYuNioUgCf-WtdMcFUa2f95K6-5aJwe6Ornk6ZnOpMqt_-LsEM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Loft Hotel Downtown Yangon truly exceeded my expectations. The location is excellent, with easy access to nearby pagodas, a mall, spas, and restaurants, making it convenient to explore the area. What really stood out to me was the exceptional service provided by the staff. They were incredibly helpful and courteous, especially Saw and the new chef in charge. Due to some restrictions in Myanmar, I had difficulty obtaining a SIM card on my first day. The staff went above and beyond by voluntarily accompanying me to a store and assisting me with my phone. On my third day, Saw even helped me find a restaurant by walking with me around the block. Their personalized service was impressive, always checking to ensure everything was okay and offering assistance whenever needed. Although the restaurant is still in the process of establishing a regular menu, they were happy to prepare dishes based on my cravings, provided the ingredients were available. I had the chance to enjoy a full-course meal, and it surpassed my expectations. Initially, I thought it seemed a bit pretentious, but the taste more than delivered, and the price was surprisingly affordable. The room was fantastic, with a chic and unique design that I loved. The staff were very welcoming and I would recommend 100%","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clarence D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I very much enjoyed this hotel.  The staff was friendly and spoke English.  The bed was comfortable, but the pillow was a bit stiff.  The room was clean and roomy--better than many of the local hotels in which I have stayed in Europe.  They have a nice restaurant with a very affordable menu.  The Shwedagon Pagoda is not all that far, but it is best to take a quick and low priced taxi.  If you do not pay ahead, bring enough cash to pay for your room and save the 3%+ CC fee.  The old colonial area is not all that far, and the Bogyoke Aung San Market is within easy walking distance.  Just a 100 feet or so is a great coffee shop, and the Depending on your ability to walk, you can easily get there by foot and take it all in.  Lastly, I never felt like the area was dangerous or unsafe.  Everyone was friendly and courteous.  Ultimately, I am glad that I went to Yangon and I am glad that I skipped the big-named hotel and stayed at The Loft Hotel.","Images":null,"When":""}]

To make matters worse, the bathroom amenities were only set up for one person. When I requested additional items, the staff insisted that my booking was for a single guest. I had to show them proof from both my booking confirmation and the Trip.com request form before they only gave one additional toothbrush.Regarding non-smoking room, I again raised my concerns in the mid-afternoon, the receptionist informed me at around 8:30 PM that they could move me to another non-smoking room which I kindly declined because I dont have time to pack again as I am have other business meetings in that evening. Due to the overwhelming smoke smell and the unacceptable hygiene condition of the bedsheets, I was unable to sleep all night.As for the morning breakfast, I was once again disappointed by the poor service. I ordered an egg, but it was poorly prepared—its appearance was unappetising, almost resembling vomit. To make matters worse, when the restaurant staff brought it over, liquid from the eggs was dripping through their hands and onto the floor. It was extremely unhygienic and unacceptable.To be honest, I was deeply disappointed by the hotel’s failure to maintain even basic standards of professionalism and hygiene, let alone the expectations of a four-star establishment.I sincerely hope the hotel improves its professionalism and, most importantly, its basic hygiene. I had planned to stay again due to its convenient location near Shwedagon Pagoda, but my experience made me reconsider.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lin Latt Htun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNN4TJeWej7D7EsLXEUn_ECg_6k9f8LGJh_qg7WRntgjN3I70j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Room is clean and well organized.
