title: 100 Moon Inn
address: 50/C(4), Natmauk Lanethwe (1, 40 Nat Mauk St, Yangon 11211
descriptions: Traditionally furnished rooms, some with terraces, along with a garden & free Wi-Fi.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Brent M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfHhPp0vyvo1Wo3WY4NH1G5QOPAHGBMv_XiebXLZtHzVwVa3wkRhb3dykyKrUCZPlawDA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at 100 Moon for 2 nights after arriving in Yangon. The staff were very helpful and friendly. The room and en suite bath were clean. The bathroom was a bit basic, but fitting what you'd expect at a mid range guest house.||The location was really ideal for a few reasons. The house itself is on a quieter street in a neighbourhood so there is no traffic noise.  It's walking distance to the Shwe Dagon Pagoda, and an easy taxi to the city or restaurants around the city. And it's 45 to an hour to the airport with the traffic.||Great value for money, and a good location as a base for exploring Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Winifred66","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcKrc8e2JnTu8c7_hmoZKea10RMTDbKaR4QZbjFBwR43DXTBpqzkG_SGZrLD47rFdkvjQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This little Inn was a haven to return to after excursions to the city.  It is north of downtown but easy access to many areas.  Walkable to Shwedagon Pagoda and KanDawGyi Lake is just a 5 minute walk away with its beautiful green space to enjoy with panoramic views of Shwedagon.  A few minutes taxi ride to downtown.  Restaurant options walkable too.||Staff at 100 Moon Inn are attentive and polite and very responsive to requests.  Great breakfasts with GREAT filter coffee to start the day.  If you want something a little bit out of the busyness of downtown then try this out.  VERY clean rooms and awesomely comfortable beds.  You get more than what you pay for here. Would come back any day.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Orah M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a small, lovely, quiet hotel on a very quiet street in the Banan neighborhood which is not far from the center of town and close to one of the parks on a lake. We took a superior room which was spacious and comfortable. Breakfast in the patio downstairs was good and it's possible to order a local breakfast. WIFI worked well. The staff is wonderful and helpful. I highly recommend this hotel, especially as a getaway from the hectic, chaotic center of the city.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Douglas B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This inn is essentially a private house converted into rooms. The manager/owner speaks good English, the other helpful staff not so much.||||I had a large room with the door right next to the entrance. It was still quiet and with the property off the road and surrounded by trees it is mostly the sounds of birds that might disturb one. The room was clean, bed comfortable, a/c, fridge, safe. Bathroom smallish but fine, big shower. Soap, shampoo provided.||||TV but only 2 channels - movies and lifestyle. But good wifi. No restaurant on site but a good and popular local restaurant within 5min walk. Western restaurants a bit further. Drinks available at the inn. Breakfast consists of 4 choices - 3 local meals or a plain omelette served with toast and fruit. ||||Can walk to park and lake; could walk to pagoda and town if keen on walking but calling a taxi could be easier.||||Needed to stay in Yangon an extra day for rest and had no problem deciding to stay on that extra day at 100 Moon Inn. If you are after being closer to the nightlife action this might not be the place for you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saran W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We decided to book this hotel based on the review from Trip advisor website. We stayed there for three nights. The room is larger than my expectation. The location is on the alley of the street , privacy, quiet, and its near to downtown. The breakfast is fantastic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Truc V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Positives||- Large triple room, very spacious albeit a bit dark||- One queen bed and a large single bed||- Quite place away from the busy, dusty streets||- The owner will buy and deliver food from the closest Chinese restaurant for you||- One of the boys will run and fetch a taxi for you when requested||- Decent house, tastefully decorated, comfortable room and comfy beds, friendly staff||||||1) Sunday night mosquito fumigation||On our very first night there, between 1800-1900 hours just after putting baby to sleep, as I was sitting on the bed I heard this deafening lawn mower noise coming closer and closer to us, then it stopped.  And all of the sudden it was hard to breath and I could not see much of the sitting area because the whole room was filled with smoke!  I quickly grabbed the sleeping baby, ran out of the room upstairs to the reception area to ask what was wrong!  With very limited English the owner later managed to tell me that it was the regular Sunday night mosquito fumigation and somehow the fumes got into our room.||||He knew about it and yet did nothing to warn us, knowing full well that we checked in with a small baby.||||Not acceptable.||||||2) Room change||Understandably I was very worried about the toxicity of the fumes and our baby, requested that we change room to another one that's the same size and setup.  There was only one tripple room, all other rooms were smaller which meant a downgrade, but the owner refused to give a discount even if we downgrade to a smaller room to avoid the smoke.||We ended up having to wait until the smoke cleared, coming back to and sleeping in the same room that night.||||Such welcoming event on our first night.  It was an extremely stressful experience, had we not pre-paid for the 3 nights we would have moved hotel the very next morning!||||Two big thumbs down for this experience and the owner's customer service alone.  Well, no customer service to speak of.||||||3) Too many mosquitoes, no mosquito net!||So with mosquitoes everywhere outside, and quite a few inside the room all the three of us got bitten everynight.  Our poor one year old baby, she got bitten every night, on her legs, arms and face.||||Definitely don't recommend staying here with kids.  You get eaten alive by mosquitoes in the room.||||||4) Housekeeping \u0026 room cleaning||Even though fresh towels and sheets are changed everyday, however there is a lot left to be desired in the housekeeping department when it comes to room cleaning service.||||The mop was used for the entire room without being washed because a water bucket was nowhere to be seen during the operation.  So afterwards, even though the entire floor was mopped it still felt dirty and our feet got dirty in minutes again.||||Air freshener was used but it actually was stinky and quite suffocating!||||||5) No room service for breakfast||Despite having pre-ordered our breakfasts, the next morning when I rang reception, the owner refused to have breakfast brought to our room.  We ended up feeding our baby in the room, then having breakfast in the courtyard later, which pretty much took the whole morning.  By the time we finished breakfast and managed to get out of the house, it was 11am!||Subsequent mornings, after even more repeat requests they reluctantly brought breakfasts to our room so we could eat and feed our child at the same time to save time.||||It should not be that difficult with room service, it's pretty normal, especially given we have a little baby with us.||||This BnB is not at all baby friendly.||||||6) Very limited English||No one at this BnB could speak English adequately so they can make themselves understood, nor could they understand my requests without me having to repeat them for the nth time.||- the young boys could understand some but not speak English at all||- the owner misunderstood my request for dinner, ordered too many dishes for 2 people||- the owner misunderstood my request for taxi to the airport, instead of waiting for me to call reception around 10am, a taxi was ordered in exact at 10am.  The taxi driver ended up waiting for nearly an hour before we were ready.||||||It's a family business, so obviously they tried their best but their service still need many improvements to make it worth while.||||||Overall, it was barely a satisfactory stay given the problems described above.  The fact the fumes from the mosquito fumigation got into our room while baby was sleeping and the owner did not let us know in advance was unacceptable.  Adequate English is a must to ensure sufficient communication.||||The best tips I can give you||Tip #1: if you are planning to stay on a Sunday night, check with them about mosquito fumigation||Tip #2: use an English/Burmese translator (such as Google Translate) to avoid misunderstandings||Tip #3: the BnB is always almost empty, so you probably don't need to book so many nights in advance.  Stay for a couple of nights first and see if it's worth the budget option.||||Recommendation?  Only if the owner improves on those points mentioned above, then yes.||||For me, I will be staying elsewhere next time around.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sharon B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very comfortable bed, serviceable room with everything we needed, brilliant breakfast, super helpful staff, easy access to downtown Yangon via taxi, close walk to Ocean Supermarket.  Will definitely stay again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Reasonable price with a private room / good WIFI /  many selection of breakfast/ hot shower / perfect location, it's near to everywhere/ the best choice for travelling into Yangon. warm hospitality. Totally recommend it","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Grand Laurel Hotel
address: MM 153/159 Bo Gyoke Aung San Rd, Yangon 11161
descriptions: Simple rooms & suites in a straightforward hotel offering a rooftop restaurant & a fitness center.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Si Thu NCA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUsXQH9RL-hFKSg81SjPm4vsPs_0732bbhrdFDCRSR4qGdttln=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a decent hotel for short staying. The rooms are quite tidy and fresh. It's nice that there's plenty of room types you can choose. Breakfast included feature is an indeed good feature. The design of the hotel is also interesting. Elevators available as well.
Customer service's also ok. They will clean your room when the staffs were asked or you can give them schedules to do it. They are also friendly as well. Oh yeah wifi's also good. U get a password for the wifi everyday. It's kinda like a one-day-use wifi to you do have to enter the new password everyday. For the breakfast, the menu's also interesting with local foods like mont-hin-gah to western foods like toast and butter or American breakfast. Overall, it's a nice hotel with fair price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LJH37","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"While it's nothing fancy, this hotel has it's own kind of charm.
